SIMPLE: christcross
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Christcross
<hw>Christ"cross`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>The
mark of the cross, as cut, painted, written, or stamped on certain
objects, -- sometimes as the sign of 12 o'clock on a dial.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The fescue of the dial is upon the <qex>christcross</qex> of
noon.</q> <rj><qau>Old Play. Nares.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>The beginning and the ending.</def>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark> <rj><au>Quarles.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Christcross-row</ent>⟦br⟧
